{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Grease 6 Thermomix® ramekins size 1 and place 1 sage leaf in the base of each.","Place hazelnuts in mixing bowl and chop <b>6 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place Parmesan and 3 sage leaves in mixing bowl then grate <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Transfer to another bowl and set aside.","Place garlic, onions and oil in mixing bowl then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <b>5 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>. Transfer to a third bowl and set aside.","Place ricotta, reserved Parmesan mixture, egg, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Add reserved onion mixture and stir <b>10 sec\/\/speed 2<b>. Finish stirring by hand with spatula if necessary. Divide mixture between prepared ramekins and sprinkle over reserved chopped hazelnuts. Cover each ramekin with heat-resistant cling film and place in Varoma dish. Clean mixing bowl.","Place water in mixing bowl, place covered Varoma into position and steam <b>30 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove Varoma, carefully remove Varoma lid and leave cakes to cool for approx. 10 minutes. Carefully remove cling film, unmould cakes with a table knife and serve each with 1 tsp cranberry compote."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["9 fresh sage leaves","40 g hazelnuts","50 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (2 cm)","1 garlic clove","70 g onions, quartered","20 g vegetable oil, plus extra for greasing","250 g ricotta cheese","1 medium egg","3 pinches fine sea salt","3 pinches ground black pepper","500 g water","6 tsp wild cranberry compote"]}],"id":"r365601","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-O-BgS5oJlBk\/XZMvXafo4II\/AAAAAAAAaQ4\/DMO94kYciGQAL-VmPrn-BZenY8uab0D6gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_e21LXqmKQCwGkKEQ.png","title":"Onion Ricotta Cakes with Sage","publishedAt":"2018-10-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9 g","fat":"16 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"4 g","calories":"838 kJ \/ 200 kcal"},"u